        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down.</hi> | Beckenham | <hi rend="print">Kent. S.E.</hi></placeName>
                    <date>March 15<hi rend="superscript">th</hi></date>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I thank you for your kind letter. You show no signs of your four score years in your letter or in the newspaper article, which seems written with all your pristine vigour.—<ref target="#foot.f2"/> My health keeps very indifferent &amp; every exertion fatigues me, so that I doubt whether I shall be good for much more. Your parable of the Damascus woman is quite new to me &amp; very striking.<ref target="#foot.f3"/></p>
<p>I sincerely wish you a happy meeting with your son.—<ref target="#foot.f4"/> I have many letters to write, so pray excuse my brevity, &amp; believe me | with respect | yours faithfully | Ch. Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="tnotes">
                <note xml:id="tnote.n1">0.1 Beckenham] <hi rend="italic">before del</hi> ‘<hi rend="italic">Bromley.</hi>’ </note>
            </div>

            
            
            
            
            
